author: Nicola Agius
title: Chloe Ferry, Kim Woodburn and Jessica Cunningham join Celebrity Big Brother line-up as late arrivals
text:
Celebrity Big Brother welcomed three new housemates this evening. 
Chloe Ferry, Kim Woodburn and Jessica Cunningham have joined this year's line-up as late arrivals. 
The trio entered the house wearing masks as the "Weekend From Hell" kicked off - which will see another housemate evicted on Sunday. 
When they revealed their identities, the current housemates seemed delighted as they welcomed them into them into the group. Celebrity Big Brother welcomed three new housemates this evening Chloe Ferry, Kim Woodburn and Jessica Cunningham have joined this year's line-up as late arrivals (Photo: Channel 5) 
However, the cheers didn't last long as presenter Emma Willis had bad news - another housemate would be booted out of the competition. 
Making matters worse for this year's line-up, it was up to the housemates to decide who would be losing their place in the competition second time round. Chloe Ferrystars on Geordie Shore How will Kim cope in the CBB house? 
Austin Armacost then lost his place on the show. 
His departure came just minutes after Angie Best was eliminated by the public in the first eviction of the series. Jessica found fame on The Apprentice 
Calum Best's mum looked disappointed as Emma announced the results, confirming she was the first star of the series to get the boot. 
However, during her exit interview, she insisted she deserved to lose her place in the competition. 
She said: "I thoroughly enjoyed Big Brother , but I couldn't help but think to myself, what am I doing here. I'm 64-years-old! 
"I've never done a reality show... Thank you Big Brother , it was an amazing experience but I am glad to be sat here." Angei Best was the first housemate to be eliminated this series (Photo: Channel 5) 
Angie added: "I went in there to spend time with my son [ Calum Best ]. But nine days in a bubble with all of those emotions and people - I've had enough now. Time for mum to go and let them get on with it. 
*Celebrity Big Brother returns to Channel 5 tomorrow at 9pm Like us on Facebook
